il 24, 2023\n\nBroad Beach Road Water Quality Repair\n\n\u00be Updates:\n\nUpdates: \u0083 Construction was completed,", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 7713, "end_char_idx": 8066, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "f30ba3c7-5ff4-4282-9010-2e9bd70923bb": {"__data__": {"id_": "f30ba3c7-5ff4-4282-9010-2e9bd70923bb", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "d085eaec-33da-425d-882e-f4838b1193e6", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "cb964ae1a2debb31f53a01df1ce7b0fe03c3e84a6fad888ec2ce82998e8d0b0c", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "9103c897-45c1-4fe6-8de4-0455fcf15f9f", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "82279ae567cff118c672432219dff5761348dd4e823c1c8fef08982c53c56e3a", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "ef9d5ca9-d9fe-43ea-9fb2-16444077158e", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "2d4bf9d23999ea840923c96a11d84c8a729b83cea8b7ee8aeba21afd718c2560", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "November 2022\n\n\u0083 City Council acceptance January 2023\n\nPoint Dume Walkway Repairs\n\n\u00be\n\nUpdates: \u0083 Construction was completed November 2022\n\n\u0083 City Council acceptance January 2023\n\nPage 6 of 7\nAgenda Item # 4.B.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 8067, "end_char_idx": 8276, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "ef9d5ca9-d9fe-43ea-9fb2-16444077158e": {"__data__": {"id_": "ef9d5ca9-d9fe-43ea-9fb2-16444077158e", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "d085eaec-33da-425d-882e-f4838b1193e6", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "cb964ae1a2debb31f53a01df1ce7b0fe03c3e84a6fad888ec2ce82998e8d0b0c", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "f30ba3c7-5ff4-4282-9010-2e9bd70923bb", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "0a8fed8cde33d7eb8ebf6c424de966113a531cebb8c93f14479e98afbe1aee5f", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "bc8bfabe-0755-494e-a63a-fbf2ae14db7a", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "877c2c4878f8fed6d564b15904f942f1c90202f51537616cd653b3073a400e58", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "Capital Improvement Projects (Not Started)\n\nPCH Crosswalk Improvements at Big Rock Drive and 20326 PCH \u00be Project Description:\n\n This project was identified in the 2015 PCH Safety Study and includes the installation of overhead warning signs and raised medians on PCH. New flashing warning beacons will be installed approximately 200 feet east and west of 20326 PCH (Moonshadow\u2019s Restaurant).", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 8278, "end_char_idx": 8669, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "bc8bfabe-0755-494e-a63a-fbf2ae14db7a": {"__data__": {"id_": "bc8bfabe-0755-494e-a63a-fbf2ae14db7a", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "d085eaec-33da-425d-882e-f4838b1193e6", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "cb964ae1a2debb31f53a01df1ce7b0fe03c3e84a6fad888ec2ce82998e8d0b0c", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "ef9d5ca9-d9fe-43ea-9fb2-16444077158e", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "2d4bf9d23999ea840923c96a11d84c8a729b83cea8b7ee8aeba21afd718c2560", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "bd33fc8b-51e7-4f26-99b3-c9b7151c23e5", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "46238960c4bb9a4ad4afa7c1d980c4485537f7676039057a0aa6b19f5d92174e", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "New raised medians, along with a pedestrian refuge area, are planned for this area. A new overhead flashing \u201csignal ahead\u201d beacon will be installed 400 feet east of PCH and Big Rock Drive intersection.\n\n\u00be Project Updates:  Staff continues to work with Measure M to finalize the scope of work.\n\nStaff has also  prepared a Public Works  Quarterly Update flier.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 8670, "end_char_idx": 9028, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "bd33fc8b-51e7-4f26-99b3-c9b7151c23e5": {"__data__": {"id_": "bd33fc8b-51e7-4f26-99b3-c9b7151c23e5", "embedding": null, "metadata": {}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "d085eaec-33da-425d-882e-f4838b1193e6", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {}, "hash": "cb964ae1a2debb31f53a01df1ce7b0fe03c3e84a6fad888ec2ce82998e8d0b0c", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "bc8bfabe-0755-494e-a63a-fbf2ae14db7a", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "877c2c4878f8fed6d564b15904f942f1c90202f51537616cd653b3073a400e58", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "78210507-35ff-40cb-ae0c-b0a49ee34c56", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "85919599825e38cb1db0fef26c9a93350b6d49de086b30ab7d6e4e1650ec7a78", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "This flier will include  a variety  of  Public  Works  statistics,  including  Projects  Under  Design,  Citizen  Request, Encroachment Permits Issued, and the amount of Development Reviews performed.  The flier  will  also  include  a  \u201cProject  Spotlight\u201d  that  will  describe  a  City  capital  improvement project.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 9030, "end_char_idx": 9349, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "{metadat